14th Avenue, at the N.E. corner of 149th Street, showing an old house covered with outdoor advertising. It was owned by D. Steffens in 1873 and 1891 and at the earlier date was known as the International Hotel.
P. L. Sperr

149th Street, east side, at 14th Avenue, showing the Whitestone Station of the United States Post Office. This intersection is known as Private McKee Square.
March 5, 1932
P. L. Sperr
